{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require landlords and letting agents to offer video viewings for disabled people",
        "additional_details": "We believe that disabled people are being placed at a distinct disadvantage by not being offered reasonable and fair adjustments to the process of viewing a house for the purpose of renting and/or buying.",
        "background": "We would like the Government to require landlords and letting agents to offer video viewings for disabled people. Currently there is no specific law in place for this adjustment to be provided and this can mean disabled people spend a lot of money, time and resources trying to view places. ",
